\begin_layout Standard
SIR equations 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial_{t}s=-\beta si$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial_{t}r=\gamma i$
\end_inset

 with the conservation law 
\begin_inset Formula $1=s+i+r$
\end_inset

; thus the evolution of the epidemics plane follows the law 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\partial\ln s/\partial r=-\mathcal{R}_{0}\label{eq:main}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{R}_{0}=\beta/\gamma$
\end_inset

 is the basic reproduction number.
 Thus, defining 
\begin_inset Formula $y=\ln s$
\end_inset

, SIR epidemics have the form 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
y_{E}=\ln s_{0}-\mathcal{R}_{0}\left(r-r_{0}\right)\label{eq:straight}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

.
 Notice that an epidemics end when eq.
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:straight"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 intersect the boundary curve 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
y_{\Omega}=\ln\left(1-r\right)\label{eq:boundary}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

corresponding to 
\begin_inset Formula $r+s=1$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $i=0$
\end_inset

.
 NOTE: 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{\Omega}$
\end_inset

 is the disease-free equilibrium curve (also disease free set: 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega=\left\{ \left(s,i,r\right):i=0\land s+r=1\right\} $
\end_inset

).
 The initial state of the system at the start of an epidemics is normally
 supposed to be due to a small number of infected individuals 
\begin_inset Formula $i_{0}=\epsilon$
\end_inset

 (i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{0}=1-\epsilon$
\end_inset

) that is a vanishing fraction 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon\to0$
\end_inset

 of the population; thus, a simple epidemics in the 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(r,y\right)$
\end_inset

 plane is a straight line starting from the point 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{0}=\left(y=0,r=0\right)$
\end_inset

.
 Since the boundary is concave and its slope in 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{0}$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial_{r}y_{\Omega}|_{r=0}=-1$
\end_inset

, the epidemics will start only if there is a non-zero intersection of the
 straight line eq.
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:straight"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, i.e.
 if 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{R}_{0}>1$
\end_inset

.
 Notice that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{R}_{0}>1$
\end_inset

 is also the condition for 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{0}$
\end_inset

to be unstable; in fact, 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial_{t}i>0$
\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $s>\mathcal{R}_{0}^{-1}$
\end_inset

; since 
\begin_inset Formula $s<1$
\end_inset

 c.v.d.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Notice that we must have 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{\infty}\left(\mathcal{R}_{0},s_{0}=1\right)>\mathcal{R}_{0}^{-1}$
\end_inset

