\begin_layout Standard
To avoid overwhelming the emergency care units of national health services
 (NHSs), it is important to avoid that the number of infectious goes beyond
 a given threshold 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

.
 In the 
\begin_inset Formula $r-s$
\end_inset

 plane, this corresponds to the straight lines 
\begin_inset Formula $s=\left(1-\theta\right)-r$
\end_inset

 that are parallel to the boundary 
\begin_inset Formula $s=1-r$
\end_inset

.
 Thus, we can define the boundary
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
y^{\theta}=\log\left(1-\theta-r\right)
\]

\end_inset

.
 Thus, to avoid overwhelming a NHS, lockdown strategies have to constrain
 the dynamic in the region 
\begin_inset Formula $y^{\theta}\leq y\leq y^{\Omega}$
\end_inset

.
 Notice that for the 
\begin_inset Formula $SEIR$
\end_inset

 model this is an upper bound, since 
\begin_inset Formula $1-s-r=i+e\leq i$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

